Perceptions of DisabilitiesPrincipal Investigator: David Brocker


Research Consent Form

 

Purpose and Expectations

You are being asked to participate in a research study being conducted by David Brocker from the Psychology Department at Farmingdale State College. You must be 18 years of age or older to participate in this research. The purpose of the study is to understand student beliefs and perceptions about the concept of creepiness, or a creepy individual. If you decide to participate in the research, you will be asked to complete three questionnaires. One will ask demographic information, the second will ask about your perception of creepiness, and the third will ask you to rate faces of several people on different traits. Your participation should take approximately 15 minutes. 

 

Benefits and Risks 

While there is no direct benefit to participating in this study, however your participation will add to the body of research about the topic above. While there no anticipated physical, emotional, or social risks associated with this research beyond what one would experience in their everyday life. However, there is a possible risk of post-survey distress for some individuals (possible self-reflection), if you feel distressed as a result of participation in this study, speaking with a qualified clinician may help. If you feel that you would like assistance, please contact Campus Mental Health Services at 934-420-2006. 

 

Anonymity / Confidentiality of Data 

Data will be collected in an anonymous manner. David Brocker will not assign/award the research credit to participants. Upon completion of the survey, you will automatically receive extra credit for your participation, but your name and ID will not be associated with your questionnaires. Questionnaires will be completed without any identifying information on them. Reporting of any data or findings will be reported in aggregate so that individual responses cannot be identified. 

 

Voluntary Participation 

For participation in this research, you will receive 5 points added to one exam grade in your Psychology class. Your Professor will be notified that you should be awarded 5 points, but they will not be notified of your answers or what study you participated in. If you would like this credit to apply to a Business course, please refer to the information provided by your instructor to determine the number of extra credit points earned. Please note extra credit earned from the participant pool is only applicable to participating psychology/business courses. Your participation in this study is voluntary. You may choose not to participate in the study or to drop out at any time without consequence. If you have any questions about the research, contact the Principal Investigator at brockeda@farmingdale.edu, (934)-420-5678 or Farmingdale State College's IRB at 934-420-2687 or IRB@farmingdale.edu.

 

 


 

Please select YES if you have read and understand the information above and choose to participate in this research. 

 

If you select NO, the survey will automatically close.
